cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image quality assessment. It may also belong to multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with visual content. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) suggests that it may also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of similarity maps derived from full-reference image quality assessment methods suggests that it may also belong to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
